| **Cloud Run** | 2 vCPU, 4 GB | $155 | GCP preference |
| **Fargate Spot** | 4 vCPU, 8 GB | $48-80 | Can tolerate interruptions |

---

## **Recommendation**

For a 24/7 IT asset management application with persistence requirements:

**Best Value: AWS EC2 t3.medium ($35/month)**
- Runs Docker containers perfectly
- EBS volumes provide reliable persistent storage
- Most economical for always-on workloads
- Simple setup: install Docker, run your container, attach EBS volume
- Can use Docker Compose for easy management

**If you prefer serverless:** AWS Fargate at $87-159/month (depending on specs) removes infrastructure management but costs 2.5-4.5x more than EC2.

**Additional Considerations:**
- Add AWS Backup for EBS snapshots (~$2-3/month)
- Consider Reserved Instances for EC2 (1-year commitment saves ~30%, 3-year saves ~60%)
- T3 instances include "burstable" CPU with baseline performance - perfect for IT asset management workloads
